---
source: crates/wasm-frontend/src/components/ds/table.rs
expression: "crate::components::ds::pretty_html(&render(\"table\", \"11\", \"Table\",\nr##\"Two patterns cover everything: a <strong>definition</strong> table (no <code class=\"mono text-[12px]\">&lt;thead&gt;</code>, identifier on the left, meaning on the right) and a <strong>tabular</strong> table (labeled columns, <code class=\"mono text-[12px]\">tabular-nums</code> for figures). 13px body, 1.5px soft row separators (<code class=\"mono text-[12px]\">border-lineSoft</code>), <code class=\"mono text-[12px]\">py-3</code> rows. When the leading column is a category, use the <a href=\"#c-item-details\" class=\"text-ink-700 underline decoration-line decoration-1 underline-offset-[3px] hover:text-ink-900\">.id-http-status</a> pill family.\"##,\nTAB_ENTRIES,))"
---
<section class="pt-12 md:pt-16" id="table">
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-[600px_1fr] gap-6 md:gap-12">
    <div>
      <div class="text-[12px] mono uppercase tracking-wider text-ink-500">
        11
      </div>
      <h2 class="mt-2 text-[24px] font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Table
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-2 text-[13px] text-ink-500 leading-relaxed">
        Two patterns cover everything: a
        <strong>
          definition
        </strong>
        table (no
        <code class="mono text-[12px]">
          &lt;thead&gt;
        </code>
        , identifier on the left, meaning on the right) and a
        <strong>
          tabular
        </strong>
        table (labeled columns,
        <code class="mono text-[12px]">
          tabular-nums
        </code>
        for figures). 13px body, 1.5px soft row separators (
        <code class="mono text-[12px]">
          border-lineSoft
        </code>
        ),
        <code class="mono text-[12px]">
          py-3
        </code>
        rows. When the leading column is a category, use the
        <a href="#c-item-details" class="text-ink-700 underline decoration-line decoration-1 underline-offset-[3px] hover:text-ink-900">
          .id-http-status
        </a>
        pill family.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-12">
      <div>
        <div class="text-[12px] text-ink-500 mb-3">
          Definition · identifier and meaning
        </div>
        <div class="overflow-x-auto border-t-[1.5px] border-lineSoft">
          <table class="w-full min-w-[560px] text-[13px]">
            <tbody class="text-ink-900">
              <tr class="border-b border-lineSoft">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline whitespace-nowrap">
                  <div>
                    <span class="mono">
                      version
                    </span>
                    <span class="ml-2 text-[11px] text-ink-500">
                      string · required
                    </span>
                  </div>
                </td>
                <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                  SemVer tag, e.g.
                  <span class="mono">
                    0.2.4
                  </span>
                  .
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-lineSoft">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline whitespace-nowrap">
                  <div>
                    <span class="mono">
                      signature
                    </span>
                    <span class="ml-2 text-[11px] text-ink-500">
                      string · optional
                    </span>
                  </div>
                </td>
                <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                  Detached cosign-compatible signature, base64 encoded.
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-lineSoft">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline whitespace-nowrap">
                  <div>
                    <span class="mono">
                      --scope
                    </span>
                    <span class="ml-2 inline-flex items-baseline gap-1">
                      <code class="mono text-[11px] text-ink-700 bg-surfaceMuted px-1 py-0.5 rounded-sm">
                        user
                      </code>
                      <code class="mono text-[11px] text-ink-700 bg-surfaceMuted px-1 py-0.5 rounded-sm">
                        project
                      </code>
                      <code class="mono text-[11px] text-ink-700 bg-surfaceMuted px-1 py-0.5 rounded-sm">
                        system
                      </code>
                    </span>
                  </div>
                </td>
                <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                  Where to write the registry entry. Defaults to
                  <span class="mono">
                    user
                  </span>
                  .
                </td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="border-b border-lineSoft">
                <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline whitespace-nowrap">
                  <div>
                    <span class="mono">
                      --config
                    </span>
                    <span class="mono text-ink-400">
                      <path>
                      </span>
                      <span class="ml-2 text-[11px] text-ink-500">
                        path
                      </span>
                    </div>
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                    Override the project config file location.
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-[12px] text-ink-500">
            Used for request body fields, CLI flags, environment variables, schema docs — anywhere each row is "name + what it does." No
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              &lt;thead&gt;
            </code>
            because column labels would just repeat what the cells already show. Left column auto-sizes with
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              whitespace-nowrap
            </code>
            : mono identifier in
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              ink-900
            </code>
            (with optional
            <span class="mono text-ink-400">
              &lt;placeholder&gt;
            </span>
            in
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              ink-400
            </code>
            ), then a meta slot on the same baseline holding either an 11px
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              ink-500
            </code>
            qualifier (
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              string · required
            </code>
            ,
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              path
            </code>
            ) or enum values as small mono chips (
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              bg-surfaceMuted px-1 py-0.5 rounded-sm
            </code>
            ). Right column is reading-flow prose at
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              ink-700
            </code>
            .
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-[12px] text-ink-500 mb-3">
            Tabular · labeled columns with status and metrics
          </div>
          <div class="overflow-x-auto border-t-[1.5px] border-lineSoft">
            <table class="w-full min-w-[560px] text-[13px]">
              <thead>
                <tr class="text-ink-400">
                  <th class="text-left font-normal py-3 pr-6 w-[80px]">
                    Status
                  </th>
                  <th class="text-left font-normal py-3 pr-6 w-[180px]">
                    Code
                  </th>
                  <th class="text-right font-normal py-3 pr-6 w-[100px]">
                    Calls
                  </th>
                  <th class="text-right font-normal py-3 pr-6 w-[120px]">
                    Avg latency
                  </th>
                  <th class="text-left font-normal py-3">
                    Meaning
                  </th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody class="text-ink-900">
                <tr class="border-t-[1.5px] border-lineSoft">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline">
                    <span class="id-http-status id-http-status-2xx">
                      200
                    </span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline mono text-ink-700">
                    ok
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums">
                    1 240
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums">
                    38 ms
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                    Request succeeded.
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t-[1.5px] border-lineSoft">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline">
                    <span class="id-http-status id-http-status-4xx">
                      400
                    </span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline mono text-ink-700">
                    invalid_request
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums">
                    12
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums">
                    4 ms
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                    Malformed parameter or request body.
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t-[1.5px] border-lineSoft">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline">
                    <span class="id-http-status id-http-status-4xx">
                      401
                    </span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline mono text-ink-700">
                    unauthenticated
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums text-ink-400">
                    0
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums text-ink-400">
                    —
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                    Missing or invalid bearer token.
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr class="border-t-[1.5px] border-lineSoft">
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline">
                    <span class="id-http-status id-http-status-5xx">
                      500
                    </span>
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline mono text-ink-700">
                    internal_error
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums">
                    1
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 pr-6 align-baseline text-right tabular-nums text-negative">
                    612 ms
                  </td>
                  <td class="py-3 align-baseline text-ink-700">
                    Unexpected server-side failure.
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>
          <p class="mt-3 text-[12px] text-ink-500">
            Used when columns warrant labels — error / response code reference, telemetry, anything with multiple typed columns. Headers are quiet:
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              text-ink-400 font-normal
            </code>
            at the body type size, same case as the data — they label columns without shouting. The first body row's
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              border-t-[1.5px] border-lineSoft
            </code>
            is the only rule between header and body, identical to the row separators below it. Numeric columns get
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              tabular-nums text-right
            </code>
            ; zeros and N/A drop to
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              ink-400
            </code>
            ; negatives or out-of-band values use
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              text-negative
            </code>
            ; totals use
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              font-medium
            </code>
            . Categorical leading columns use the
            <code class="mono text-[12px]">
              .id-http-status
            </code>
            pill family in a fixed-width column so the next column aligns down the page.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
